{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"6fb21ace-d2ba-4b08-99dd-30fff630db36","content":"Use **`dotnet run`**, not `dotnet test`.\n\nThe `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.HotReload` package works with the **Microsoft Testing Platform** (which your project enables via `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport`). Hot reload requires the test app to run as a long-lived process that watches for file changes — that's what `dotnet run` provides.\n\n```bash\n# Set the env var (if not already)\nexport TESTINGPLATFORM_HOTRELOAD_ENABLED=1\n\n# Run with hot reload\ndotnet run\n```\n\nWith `dotnet run`, the process stays alive and re-executes tests when you save changes. `dotnet test` runs tests once and exits, so there's no opportunity for hot reload.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"020e6703-ba8f-45dc-95e1-05c84773d1f1","outputTokens":175,"requestId":"4C36:306175:C834E6:F7847C:6A0133D6"},"id":"1104f6d5-2302-427e-90c9-f160c5307bc1","timestamp":"2026-05-11T01:41:48.877Z","parentId":"7e422d2b-d24e-406f-8598-1cb6cc3c8eeb"}
